DEBUG LOG OVERLAY HANDOFF
Date: 2026-03-20
Owner: next agent
Scope: Integrate runtime logger stream into in-game debug view toggled by `~`.

GOAL
- Keep existing logging call-sites unchanged (`logging::debug/info/warn/error`).
- Reuse one global logging stream for:
  1) run.log file (already exists),
  2) on-screen debug overlay (new log view).
- Add `~` toggle in engine runtime to open/close log overlay mode.

CURRENT STATE (FACTS)
- Central logger: engine-core/src/logging.rs
- Current overlay: engine/src/systems/renderer.rs::apply_debug_overlay
- Debug controls: engine/src/systems/scene_lifecycle.rs::handle_debug_controls
- Debug state: engine/src/debug_features.rs (enabled + overlay_visible)
- Existing debug keys: F1 overlay, F3/F4 prev/next scene
- No global in-memory log tail API yet.

RECOMMENDED DESIGN (NO LOG CALL-SITE REWRITE)
Option A (recommended): Logger fan-out with in-memory ring buffer.
- Extend engine-core logger internals so every call to logging::log(...) still writes to file,
  and also appends a parsed/structured line into a fixed-size ring buffer.
- Expose read-only API from logging module for recent entries.
- Overlay consumes this API and renders last N lines.

Why Option A:
- No file-tail polling overhead.
- Immediate updates in same process.
- Single source of truth, no duplicated formatting logic in runtime.

Option B (fallback): Overlay tails run.log from disk using run_log_info().
- Works without logger internals changes.
- More I/O and more parsing complexity.

IMPLEMENTATION PLAN

1) Extend debug feature state
File: engine/src/debug_features.rs
- Add overlay mode state, not only bool visibility.
- Suggested model:
  - `overlay_visible: bool` (existing)
  - `overlay_mode: DebugOverlayMode` where:
    - Stats (existing 3-line overlay)
    - Logs (new log window)
  - Optional scroll offset for logs.
- Keep backward compatibility: default mode = Stats.

2) Add key handling for `~`
File: engine/src/systems/scene_lifecycle.rs
- In handle_debug_controls(...):
  - Handle `KeyCode::Char('~')` and `KeyCode::Char('`')` (keyboard layout tolerance).
  - Behavior:
    - If overlay hidden -> show overlay and switch to Logs mode.
    - If overlay visible and mode Logs -> hide overlay.
    - Optional cycle: Stats -> Logs -> hidden.
- Do not remove existing F1/F3/F4 behavior.

3) Add memory sink to logger (core change, single point)
File: engine-core/src/logging.rs
- Keep current file write path untouched.
- Add ring buffer with bounded capacity (e.g. 300-1000 entries) inside logger static state.
- On every log(...) append an entry to ring:
  - timestamp
  - level
  - target
  - message
- Add public read API:
  - `tail_recent(limit: usize) -> Vec<LogOverlayLine>`
  - optional `tail_since(cursor)` if needed later.
- Add lightweight struct for overlay consumption.
- Keep panic hook behavior unchanged.

4) Render log overlay
File: engine/src/systems/renderer.rs
- In apply_debug_overlay(...):
  - if mode == Stats -> keep existing output.
  - if mode == Logs -> render compact log viewer:
    - header line (mode + hints, e.g. `~ close`, `F1 stats`)
    - last N logs fitted to terminal size
    - clip long lines, avoid allocations per frame if possible.
- Keep it fast and deterministic.

5) Logging for overlay actions
Files:
- engine/src/systems/scene_lifecycle.rs
- engine/src/systems/renderer.rs (only if needed)
- Emit DEBUG/INFO when overlay mode changes.

NON-GOALS FOR THIS TASK
- Do not split run logs into multiple files.
- Do not migrate all engine systems to new targets now.
- Do not redesign editor overlay/help.

EDGE CASES
- Logging disabled (`--no-logs` in release):
  - Decide policy explicitly.
  - Recommended: overlay still works if in-memory ring is enabled independently of file sink.
    If not desired, show "logging disabled" in overlay.
- Very small terminal sizes:
  - Render minimal header + truncated lines.
- High-volume logs:
  - Ring buffer must drop oldest entries.
  - No unbounded growth.

PERFORMANCE NOTES
- Avoid reading run.log from disk every frame (Option A avoids this).
- Keep overlay render O(rows * cols) as now.
- tail_recent should clone only small bounded subset.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
1) Existing `logging::*` call-sites continue to work unchanged.
2) Logs still appear in `run.log` exactly as before.
3) Pressing `~` in debug-enabled run opens log overlay.
4) Overlay displays latest runtime logs in near real-time.
5) Pressing `~` again closes log overlay (or cycles as designed).
6) F1/F3/F4 still work.
7) No crashes when logging disabled or terminal resized.

MANUAL TEST CHECKLIST
- Start app in debug mode with logs enabled.
- Trigger scene transitions; verify entries visible in overlay and file.
- Trigger warning/error (e.g. missing transition target) and verify visibility.
- Resize terminal repeatedly; overlay remains stable.
- Toggle F1/F3/F4 and ~ in mixed order.
- Run with logs disabled and verify chosen fallback behavior.

